               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <t:locus xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" from="2v" to="19r">2v-19r</t:locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s15IHA">قران, Eighth ǧuz’ (8/30)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <t:locus xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" target="#2v">-2v</t:locus>وَلَوْ اَنَّنَا نَزَّلْنَا اِلَيْهِمِ المَلَيِكَةَ وَكَلَّمَهُمْ المَوْتَيْ إلخ<note>The hamza-s ‘alā al-kursī are replaced by letter yā’, but the hamza also appear under the yā’ together with its two dots. No options exist on keeboards, which could allow us to write such letter.</note>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <t:locus xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" target="#19r">-19r</t:locus>وَاِن كَانَ طَيِفَةٌ مِنْكُمْ اَمَنُوْا بِالّذِيْ اُرْسِلْتُ بِهِ وَطَيِفَةُ لَمْ يُؤْمِنُا فَاصْبِرُ حَتِّي يَحْكُمَ اللهُ بَيْنَنَا وَهْوَ خَيْرُ الحَاكِميْنَ<note>The hamza-s ‘alā al-kursī are replaced by letter yā’, but the hamza also appear under the yā’ together with its two dots. No options exist on keeboards, which could allow us to write such letter.
حَتِّي : sic ; بَيْنَنَا : a damma was once on the first nūn, but was corrected on purpose.</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>6:111-7:87. Title of sūrat al-A‘rāf rubricated. Eleven lines per page, then twelve. Ihmāl marks (rā’s). Some words completed on the following line. A lot of words were left uncompleted at the end of a line, and were rewritten in full on the next line. Deletions and corrections by a hand which could be that of the copyist. Corrections in the margin by at least another hand using a thick qalam. Two marginal corrections are maybe of ta'kīd type, when the last part of a word, which is placed at the end of a line, was writen by the main copyist on the top of the word, and was rewritten by another hand below the word.</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
